### Dependency Rules (enforce via imports, not convention)

```txt
apps/claims-portal
  → libs/ui/*, libs/claims, libs/documents, libs/auth, libs/design-system, libs/shared

libs/ui/*
  → libs/design-system, libs/shared, libs/auth (layout only)

libs/claims | libs/documents | libs/auth
  → libs/shared, libs/design-system (UI primitives only)

libs/shared
  → no domain or UI libs

libs/design-system
  → no domain libs
```

- **Apps** compose features; keep business logic out of `page.tsx` / route files.
- **Domain libs** (`claims`, `documents`, `auth`) own data hooks, types, and feature logic.
- **UI libs** (`data-grid`, `layout`) own presentation; accept data/callbacks via props.
- **API route handlers** live in `apps/claims-portal/src/app/api/` (mock backend for case study).

Run tasks through Nx: `pnpm nx dev @org/claims-portal`, `pnpm nx affected -t lint test build`.

