## Implementation Phases

### Phase 0 — Foundation

- Design tokens: `libs/design-system/src/tokens` (colors, typography, spacing, radius, shadows)
- Light/dark theme; shadcn/ui base components
- ESLint, Prettier, Husky, Commitlint

### Phase 1 — Application Shell (`@org/layout`, `@org/design-system`)

- Header, sidebar, breadcrumb, user profile
- Global: page loader, error boundary, empty state, permission wrapper
- Zustand: theme, sidebar, selected claim, workspace panel state

### Phase 2 — Authentication & RBAC (`@org/auth`)

- Mock login; JWT/session parsing; protected routes
- `usePermission()`, `<Can>`; role-based action visibility

### Phase 3 — Claims Dashboard (`@org/data-grid`, `@org/claims`)

- Server-paginated grid with TanStack Table + Virtual
- Filters: claim number, status, assignee; debounced search
- Row actions: edit, delete, assign (permission-gated)
- Bulk selection, column visibility
- 50,000 mock records via API; justify **server pagination + row virtualization** in docs

### Phase 4 — Mock Backend (`apps/claims-portal/src/app/api`)

```http
GET    /api/claims              # paginated, filtered, sorted
GET    /api/claims/:id
PUT    /api/claims/:id
DELETE /api/claims/:id
GET    /api/documents/:id       # metadata + page range URLs
POST   /api/comments
GET    /api/comments
POST   /api/jobs/split
POST   /api/jobs/merge
GET    /api/jobs/:id            # progress polling
```

- Fake DB, artificial delays, configurable error rates

### Phase 5 — Document Workspace (`@org/documents`, `@org/layout`)

```txt
Toolbar
Document Viewer (PDF)
Comments / Annotations Panel
```

- PDF viewer: page nav, zoom, rotate; metadata (page count, size, modified)
- Smooth grid → workspace transition with loading/progress

### Phase 6 — Large Document Strategy (`@org/documents`)

- Page virtualization, lazy page load, skeleton pages, memory cleanup
- Range/chunked fetching; target smooth scroll at low memory

### Phase 7 — Comments & Annotations (`@org/documents`)

- Page-level comments: add, edit, delete
- Annotation layer (mock): highlight, rectangle, sticky note

### Phase 8 — Split / Merge Workflow (`@org/documents`)

- Split: select page ranges → job; Merge: select documents → job
- Progress tracking (0 → 25 → 50 → 75 → 100%); cancel/retry on failure

### Phase 9 — Performance Pass

- Route/component/dialog lazy loading; React.memo where profiling shows benefit
- Query cache tuning; prefetch strategies; bundle analysis

### Phase 10 — PWA & Offline (optional stretch)

- Workbox: cache static assets + claims list API
- Offline fallback screen

### Phase 11 — Responsive UX

- Desktop: full workspace; Tablet: collapsible panels; Mobile: dashboard + read-only viewer

### Phase 12 — Architecture Documentation

- Layer diagram (Presentation → Business → Data → Infrastructure)
- Trade-off matrix (see below); README with run/deploy instructions

